HEADWORD: Fallible
<hw>Fal"li*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>fallibilis</ets>, fr. L. <ets>fallere</ets> to deceive: cf. F.
<ets>faillible</ets>. See <er>Fail</er>.]</ety> <def>Liable to fail,
mistake, or err; liable to deceive or to be deceived; <as>as, all men
are <ex>fallible</ex>; our opinions and hopes are
<ex>fallible</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

